——Matinaez with reference to the district in which he was born. Cf. 1, 28, 3.

30 f. plurimum: with laborem. —circa nemus, etc.: his favorite Tivoli; cf. 2, 6, 5 ff.——Tiburis: modifying both nemus and ripas. —operosa parvus: Intr. 26.

33 f. concines: with Caesarem in the following verse, bearing the emphasis. ‘Caesar shall be sung. but in a different strain than that of which I am master.'—-maiore . . . plectro: ele. ‘of a grander style ’ς cf. 2, 1, 40 leviore plec- tro.
